Subject: RE: [VB] gas mileage

 One of the first Mexican 1600 I installed over four years ago still gets an
average of 25-28 mpg.  This is a new Mexican long block with duel Kadrons
and 1.25 ratio rockers. The trans is a Rancho 3.88 with an 82 4th gear. It
is in a 64 21 window Deluxe that gets driven daily 80 plus miles rt in L A,
and is used for surf trips, home depot runs, etc.
 It has over 50,000 maybe 60,000 by now and the only problem has been a worn
out fuel pump rod.


ronnie

ps. oil change and valve adjustment every 2500 to 3000 miles, with the
valves rarely needing adjustment

